  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/transportation/\" rel=\"tag\">交通相关</a>, <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/wearables/\" rel=\"tag\">佩戴产品</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"cn.engadget.com/2014/01/18/traffic-ticket-for-driving-with-google-glass-gets-dismissed-in-c/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/6827cafb1ce73ac2de6688d611121306/glass.jpg\" /></a></div>\n<br />\n话说去年的十月时，有一位名为 Cecilia Abadie、戴着 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/GoogleGlass/\">Google Glass</a> 的女士在加州驾驶之时，突然被交通警员截停并<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/10/31/driver-picks-up-ticket-for-wearing-google-glass-at-the-wheel/2\">发出罚单</a>，理由是超速和在驾驶时有萤幕放在驾驶者的眼前。事后法官 John Blair 在庭上指出没有证据显示 Abadie 女士在驾驶时有操作 Google Glass，加上没有专家出席证明警方的（超速）读数，所以在证据不足之下他决定取消这张罚单。所以，真的不知道这次是法律帮了 Abadie，还是幸运之神出手了。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/01/16/traffic-ticket-for-driving-with-google-glass-gets-dismissed-in-c/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/17/us-usa-googleglass-trial-dismissal-idUSBREA0F1XR20140117\">Reuters</a><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/18/google-glass/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20810717/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/18/google-glass/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
